  "prompt": "Is it good to have Milk during fever?",
  "response": "Generally, it is not recommended to drink milk during a fever. Here are some reasons:\n\n1. Potential drawbacks:\n- Milk can increase mucus production\n- May cause digestive discomfort\n- Can be harder to digest when you're sick\n- Could worsen symptoms for some people\n\n2. Better alternatives during fever:\n- Water\n- Herbal tea\n- Clear broths\n- Electrolyte drinks\n- Warm water with honey and lemon\n\n3. When milk might be acceptable:\n- If you tolerate it well\n- If you need protein and calories\n- If you don't experience increased mucus or digestive issues\n\n4. Important considerations:\n- Stay hydrated\n- Listen to your body\n- Consult a doctor if fever persists\n- Consider your individual tolerance\n\n5. If you want dairy:\n- Choose easily digestible options\n- Consider yogurt with probiotics\n- Use small quantities\n\nRemember, individual responses can vary, so pay attention to how your body reacts. Always prioritize hydration and rest during a fever.",
